<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 23 at 4:12PM MST  by NWS Missoula</headline>
<description>...Intense snow showers will impact portions of southeastern
Missoula, northern Granite and west central Powell Counties through
545 PM MST...
At 409 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking a line of intense snow
showers along a strong cold front extending along Interstate 90 from
Clinton to Drummond.  And Highway 200 from Bonner to Ovando, and
Highway 12 to Helmville. Movement was east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Visibility one-half mile or less and winds in excess of 40
mph.
IMPACT...Low visibility could result in dangerous driving
conditions. Expect quickly changing road conditions with
rain changing to snow.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
